/**
 * Uploads a resume for redacting. When successful, returns an `identifier` in the response for subsequent use with the [/redacted_resumes/{identifier}](#operation/getRedactedResume) endpoint to check processing status and retrieve results.
 *
 * @param options - The options parameters.
 */
members.name: createRedactedResume

members.docComment:
/**
 * Uploads a resume for reformatting. When successful, returns an `identifier` in the response for subsequent use with the [/reformatted_resumes/{identifier}](#operation/getReformattedResume) endpoint to check processing status and retrieve results.
 *
 * @param resumeFormat - Identifier of the format used
 *
 * @param options - The options parameters.
 */
members.name: createReformattedResume

members.docComment:
/**
 * Uploads a resume for parsing. When successful, returns an `identifier` in the response for subsequent use with the [/resumes/{identifier}](#operation/getResume) endpoint to check processing status and retrieve results.
 *
 * @param options - The options parameters.
 */
members.name: createResume

members.docComment:

 * Deletes the specified resume from the database

 *
 * @param options - The options parameters.
 */
members.name: deleteRedactedResume

 *

 *

 */
members.name: deleteReformattedResume

 *

 *

 */
members.name: deleteResume

members.docComment:

 * Returns all the redacted resume information for that resume
 *

 */
members.name: getAllRedactedResumes

 *

 */
members.name: getAllReformattedResumes

members.docComment:
/**
 * Returns all the resume formats
 *
 * @param options - The options parameters.
 */
members.name: getAllResumeFormats

members.docComment:
/**
 * Returns all the resume summaries for that user, limited to 300 per page.
 *
 * @param options - The options parameters.
 */
members.name: getAllResumes

members.docComment:
/**
 * Returns all the redaction results for that resume if processing is completed. The `identifier` is the unique ID returned after POST-ing the resume via the [/redacted_resumes](#operation/createRedactedResume) endpoint.
 *
 * @param identifier - Document identifier
 *
 * @param options - The options parameters.
 */
members.name: getRedactedResume

members.docComment:
/**
 * Returns all the reformatting results for that resume if processing is completed. The `identifier` is the unique ID returned after POST-ing the resume via the [/reformatted_resumes](#operation/createReformattedResume) endpoint.
 *
 * @param identifier - Document identifier
 *
 * @param options - The options parameters.
 */
members.name: getReformattedResume

members.docComment:
/**
 * Returns all the parse results for that resume if processing is completed. The `identifier` is the unique ID returned after POST-ing the resume via the [/resumes](#operation/createResume) endpoint.
 *
 * @param identifier - Document identifier
 *
 * @param options - The options parameters.
 */
members.name: getResume
